# Core Project Guardrails

## Absolute Priority

This website is SEO-first, performance-first, and Astro-first.

Priority order:

1. SEO and indexability
2. Minimal initial JavaScript
3. Useful HTML without JavaScript
4. Fast mobile performance
5. Lightweight, modern, consistent UI
6. Forms visible before wallet connection
7. Wallet/Reown/Solana SDK lazy-loaded only after user action

If a feature makes public pages heavier, less indexable, or more client-side, reject it unless explicitly approved.

---

## Stack

Use:

- Astro
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Static Astro components for public layout
- React islands only for truly interactive tool forms or wallet/action flows
- React Hook Form + Zod only inside form islands

Do not use:

- Full React SPA
- React for header/sidebar/footer
- Ant Design
- MUI
- Chakra
- HeroUI/NextUI
- Flowbite React
- Rewind UI package
- Framer Motion
- global animation libraries
- global wallet providers
- global Reown initialization
- global Solana SDK imports

---

## Change Scope Rule

When asked to modify one area, modify only that area.

Examples:

- If asked to polish Header, do not redesign Sidebar/Footer.
- If asked to polish modals, do not refactor wallet logic.
- If asked to fix styling, do not add dependencies.
- If asked to improve UI, do not increase JavaScript.
- If asked to refactor, do not redesign visuals unless requested.

Do not create new components, new scripts, or new architecture unless explicitly requested.

---

## Astro Layout Rule

These must remain Astro/static:

- `src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro`
- `src/components/layout/Header.astro`
- `src/components/layout/Sidebar.astro`
- `src/components/layout/Footer.astro`
- SEO content sections
- FAQs
- breadcrumbs
- related links
- static cards
- warnings and safety notes

Do not hydrate static navigation.

Header/sidebar/footer must not import React UI libraries, wallet libraries, Reown, Solana SDK, Raydium, Meteora, Orca, Jito, or transaction logic.

---

## Initial JavaScript Rule

Initial JS must stay as close to zero as possible.

Allowed tiny JS only for:

- theme persistence
- mobile sidebar open/close
- desktop sidebar collapsed state
- header settings/modal open/close only when already implemented
- wallet button click trigger

Do not add global layout scripts.

Do not bundle:

- `@reown/appkit`
- `@reown/appkit-adapter-solana`
- `@solana/web3.js`
- `@solana/spl-token`
- wallet-adapter packages
- Raydium/Meteora/Orca/Jito SDKs

---

## Wallet / Reown Rule

Header may show a wallet button, but wallet code must load only after explicit user click.

Allowed:

- Static Astro wallet button
- Tiny inline click handler
- Dynamic import after click: `import("../../lib/wallet/reown-client")`

Only this file may import Reown packages:

```txt
src/lib/wallet/reown-client.ts
```

Never:

- initialize Reown on page load
- initialize Reown in Astro frontmatter
- initialize Reown in layout/header/sidebar/footer
- use global wallet provider
- load Reown via `client:load`, `client:idle`, or global React island unless explicitly approved

Forms must remain visible and fillable before wallet connection.

Wallet is required only for the final transaction action.

---

## Design Direction

The UI must feel:

- serious
- modern
- clean
- technical
- trustworthy
- calm
- lightweight
- user-friendly

Avoid:

- crypto casino style
- excessive neon
- huge gradients
- glassmorphism everywhere
- oversized controls
- tiny unreadable gray text
- decorative clutter
- dashboard-heavy UI
- random one-off styles

Use:

- subtle borders
- soft surfaces
- clear typography
- compact controls
- readable spacing
- simple active states
- one main blue/cyan accent
- violet only for premium/PRO states
- semantic warning/danger colors

---

## Layout Sizing

Use shared layout tokens.

Current header height:

```css
--header-height: 3.5rem;
```

Do not hardcode:

- `top-16`
- `h-16`
- `4rem`
- `64px`

for layout positioning unless `--header-height` is also updated intentionally.

Sidebar and mobile backdrop must use:

```css
top: var(--header-height);
height: calc(100vh - var(--header-height));
```

Desktop sidebar collapsed width must use:

```css
--sidebar-collapsed-width
```

---

## Visual Token Rule

Use `src/styles/tokens.css` as the source of truth for:

- colors
- surfaces
- borders
- radius
- shadows
- control heights
- layout sizes
- focus rings

Do not create random hardcoded colors or radii inside components.

Allowed:

- Tailwind spacing and responsive utilities from the approved scale
- small layout utilities like `gap-2`, `px-4`, `text-sm`
- one-off values only when they solve a specific responsive issue and are not reusable

Do not create a new token unless it will be reused in at least 3 places.

---

## Component Scale

Use these defaults unless explicitly requested otherwise:

Header:

- height: `var(--header-height)` / 56px
- controls: 38px to 40px
- icon buttons: 40px
- no heavy shadow

Sidebar:

- width: `var(--sidebar-width)`
- item height: 38px to 42px
- icon box: 28px to 32px
- text: 13px to 14px
- collapsed styles only inside desktop media query

Footer:

- static Astro HTML
- no JS
- 3 to 4 useful columns
- clear internal links
- not oversized

Buttons:

- compact controls: 38px to 40px
- normal buttons: 44px
- large CTA: 46px to 48px
- no default shadow

Modals/sheets:

- shell radius: 24px
- inner card radius: 16px to 20px
- desktop Fee modal width: 540px to 580px
- desktop PRO modal width: 620px to 660px
- close button: 40px by 40px
- title: 18px to 22px
- subtitle/helper text: 13px to 14px
- row labels: 14px to 15px
- supporting text: 12px to 13px

Mobile:

- touch targets at least 44px
- no horizontal scroll
- compact, not chunky
- mobile sheets should feel consistent with desktop modals

---

## Typography

Use one sans-serif stack.

Do not load external Google Fonts at runtime.

Do not use decorative fonts.

Default scale:

- body: `text-base leading-7`
- nav/sidebar: `text-sm`
- labels: `text-sm font-medium`
- helper text: `text-xs leading-5`
- card titles: `text-base` or `text-lg font-semibold`
- section headings: `text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold`
- page H1: `text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight`
- modal title: `text-lg` to `text-xl font-semibold`

Avoid:

- `font-black`
- `font-extrabold`
- giant text in modals
- tiny muted text for important instructions

---

## Color Usage

Primary action:

- blue/cyan

Premium / PRO:

- violet accent for selected premium states
- CTA may remain blue/cyan if it is the main action

Network/success:

- emerald/cyan indicator only

Danger:

- red

Warning:

- amber

Do not use Solana neon green as the dominant UI color.

---

## Animation Rule

No motion animations.

Do not use:

- transform animation
- scale hover
- slide animation
- fade animation
- animated gradient
- page transition

Allowed only if needed:

- `transition-colors`
- max 150ms
- hover/focus border/background color only

If strict no-animation is requested, remove transitions entirely.

---

## Accessibility

Interactive controls must be real buttons or links.

Required:

- `aria-label` for icon-only buttons
- `aria-expanded` for menus
- `aria-controls` for controlled panels
- visible focus styles
- readable contrast in light and dark mode
- keyboard closable dialogs/menus where JS exists
- Escape closes modals/menus where JS exists

Do not use clickable divs.

---

## Icons

Use:

- `@lucide/astro` for static Astro UI icons
- local inline SVGs for protocol logos

Do not use:

- `react-icons`
- icon fonts
- animated icons
- global icon imports

Icon sizes:

- sidebar icons: 16px to 18px
- card icons: 20px
- hero/tool icons: 24px to 32px max

Decorative icons need `aria-hidden="true"`.

Meaningful icon-only buttons need accessible labels.

---

## SEO Public Page Rule

Public pages must be understandable in raw HTML.

`view-source:` should show:

- title
- meta description
- canonical
- H1
- intro
- tool explanation
- warnings/safety notes
- FAQ
- related tools
- internal links
- footer links

Do not put SEO content only inside React islands.

---

## Verification Before Done

Before saying the task is complete:

- run build
- check no new dependency was added
- check no React was added to header/sidebar/footer
- check no wallet/Reown/Solana import leaked into layout/static UI
- check light and dark mode
- check mobile width
- check no horizontal scroll
- check initial JS did not increase unnecessarily
- check `view-source` still contains meaningful HTML

For wallet-related work, search build/source for:

```txt
@reown
@solana
wallet-adapter
web3.js
spl-token
```

These must not appear in the initial public layout bundle.
